monthly_deaths$period2<-recode(monthly_deaths$period, 'Before'="0", 'After'="1")
mod<-lm(monthly_deaths$infant_mor~monthly_deaths$period2)

Question 4: Here, I run a t-test to see if the effect of handwashing on IMR is significant. The results show that at 95% confidence level, the null hypothesis is to be rejected: the means of IMR before and after handwashing are significantly different 

t.test(monthly_deaths$infant_mor~monthly_deaths$period2, mu=0, alt="two.sided", conf=0.95, var.ef=F, paired=F)

Question 5: Here, I create the radarchart showing the seasonality of IMR

monthly_deaths$month1<-strftime(monthly_deaths$date, "%b")


data1<-monthly_deaths %>% group_by(month1) %>% summarize(mean_imr=mean(infant_mor)) %>% pivot_wider(names_from = month1, values_from = mean_imr, names_sort = TRUE) 
data1<-rbind(rep(0.1216015,10), rep(0.04877752,10), data1) 


radarchart(data1[,c(5,3,10,11,12,2,6,7,9,1,8,4)], axistype=1, seg=3, title="Average IMR by Month", pcol=rgb(0.2,0.5,0.5,0.9) , plwd=0.5 , cglcol="grey", cglty=6, axislabcol="black", caxislabels=seq(0,0.15,0.05), cglwd=1, vlcex=0.8, calcex = 0.4)
